verses.text_plain: Moreover David and the captains of the host separated to the service of the sons of Asaph, and of Heman, and of Jeduthun, who should prophesy with harps, with psalteries, and with cymbals: and the number of the workmen according to their service was:
verses.verse_html: 1Moreover David and the captains of the host separated to the service of the sons of Asaph, and of Heman, and of Jeduthun, who should prophesy with harps, with psalteries, and with cymbals: and the number of the workmen according to their service was:

verses.text_plain: Of the sons of Asaph; Zaccur, and Joseph, and Nethaniah, and Asarelah, the sons of Asaph under the hands of Asaph, which prophesied according to the order of the king.
verses.verse_html:
2Of the sons of Asaph; Zaccur, and Joseph, and Nethaniah, and Asarelah, the sons of Asaph under the hands of Asaph, which prophesied according to the order of the king. ▼
▼ Asarelah: otherwise called Jesharelah
 , ▼
▼ according…: Heb. by the hands of the king

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Asarelah: otherwise called Jesharelah

footnotes.body_text: ▼ according…: Heb. by the hands of the king
footnotes.body_html: ▼ according…: Heb. by the hands of the king

verses.text_plain: Of Jeduthun: the sons of Jeduthun; Gedaliah, and Zeri, and Jeshaiah, Hashabiah, and Mattithiah, six, under the hands of their father Jeduthun, who prophesied with a harp, to give thanks and to praise the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
3Of Jeduthun: the sons of Jeduthun; Gedaliah, and Zeri, and Jeshaiah, Hashabiah, and Mattithiah, six, under the hands of their father Jeduthun, who prophesied with a harp, to give thanks and to praise the Lord. ▼
▼ Zeri: or, Izri

verses.text_plain: Of Heman: the sons of Heman; Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shebuel, and Jerimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti, and Romamti–ezer, Joshbekashah, Mallothi, Hothir, and Mahazioth:
verses.verse_html:
4Of Heman: the sons of Heman; Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shebuel, and Jerimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti, and Romamti–ezer, Joshbekashah, Mallothi, Hothir, and Mahazioth: ▼
▼ Uzziel: also called, Azareel
 , ▼
▼ Shebuel: also called, Shubael

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Uzziel: also called, Azareel
▼ Shebuel: also called, Shubael

verses.text_plain: All these were the sons of Heman the king’s seer in the words of God, to lift up the horn. And God gave to Heman fourteen sons and three daughters.
verses.verse_html:
5All these were the sons of Heman the king’s seer in the words of God, to lift up the horn. And God gave to Heman fourteen sons and three daughters. ▼
▼ words: or, matters

verses.text_plain: All these were under the hands of their father for song in the house of the Lord, with cymbals, psalteries, and harps, for the service of the house of God, according to the king’s order to Asaph, Jeduthun, and Heman.
verses.verse_html:
6All these were under the hands of their father for song in the house of the Lord, with cymbals, psalteries, and harps, for the service of the house of God, according to the king’s order to Asaph, Jeduthun, and Heman. ▼
▼ according…: Heb. by the hands of the king

footnotes.body_text: ▼ according…: Heb. by the hands of the king
footnotes.body_html: ▼ according…: Heb. by the hands of the king

verses.text_plain: So the number of them, with their brethren that were instructed in the songs of the Lord, even all that were cunning, was two hundred fourscore and eight.
verses.verse_html: 7So the number of them, with their brethren that were instructed in the songs of the Lord, even all that were cunning, was two hundred fourscore and eight.

verses.text_plain: And they cast lots, ward against ward, as well the small as the great, the teacher as the scholar.
verses.verse_html: 8And they cast lots, ward against ward, as well the small as the great, the teacher as the scholar.

verses.text_plain: Now the first lot came forth for Asaph to Joseph: the second to Gedaliah, who with his brethren and sons were twelve:
verses.verse_html: 9Now the first lot came forth for Asaph to Joseph: the second to Gedaliah, who with his brethren and sons were twelve:
